title: For Sale:  AK bolt carriers w/ one 'Tapco USA' made Chrome gas piston.
postcontent:
I have two brand new never used AK/AKM bolt carriers for 7.62x39 rifles.

These are replacement parts that were never installed in a firearm, and have no serial number engraved. The bolt carriers online run 70-100 dollars each at APEX gun parts of Brownells, NOT including shipping.
http://www.brownells.com/rifle-parts/bolt-parts/bolts/bolt-carrier-prod41491.aspx?ttver=2
https://www.apexgunparts.com/product_info.php/cPath/107/products_id/1937

These are great spare replacement parts to keep on hand if you own a AK or AKM, because this is a part for AK's that is not being made inside of the USA and can only be obtained from overseas. The Bolt carrier takes the constant shock from the gas piston forcing it open and closed, and this causes the carrier to fracture occasionally. I have sold off my AK and no longer need the spares. Without a functioning bolt carrier, your rifle will be a decoration.

I will sell each carrier for $40 each, 
but if you buy both of the carriers at $40 each, I will include the TAPCO chrome gas piston free for a total of $80 for all three of the spare AR parts. 
You are getting two NOS AK bolt carriers and a US made gas piston for the price of one stripped bolt carrier available anywhere online.
